and avoid their bankruptcy.

00:10:46.300 --> 00:10:48.310
It was a one-on-one coaching
session, that's all we had.

00:10:48.310 --> 00:10:49.250
- Yep.

00:10:49.250 --> 00:10:50.877
- And then I would see them six
months later and I would go,

00:10:50.877 --> 00:10:51.710
How's it going?

00:10:51.710 --> 00:10:52.900
"Oh, we filed bankruptcy."

00:10:52.900 --> 00:10:53.908
What?

00:10:53.908 --> 00:10:56.690
You know, I had all the math done for you.

00:10:56.690 --> 00:10:58.460
And it wasn't a math thing.

00:10:58.460 --> 00:10:59.293
- Yep.

00:10:59.293 --> 00:11:00.640
- It was a behavior thing.

00:11:00.640 --> 00:11:02.690
The stuff that was going on in their lives

00:11:02.690 --> 00:11:04.600
was still going on in their lives,

00:11:04.600 --> 00:11:08.200
and if you don't change the
person, the math doesn't change.

00:11:08.200 --> 00:11:09.920
When people change, numbers change.

00:11:09.920 --> 00:11:11.050
That's what Hogan says.

00:11:11.050 --> 00:11:12.980
Not when numbers change, people change.

00:11:12.980 --> 00:11:14.040
It doesn't go that way.

00:11:14.040 --> 00:11:16.860
So, what we figured out
was that personal finance,

00:11:16.860 --> 00:11:17.700
and we say it all the time,

00:11:17.700 --> 00:11:22.010
is 80% behavior, 20% head knowledge.

00:11:22.010 --> 00:11:24.710
The problem is not math.

00:11:24.710 --> 00:11:27.930
The problem is me, I'm
the geek, I'm the guy.

00:11:27.930 --> 00:11:31.200
When the problem is
chocolate chip cookies,

00:11:31.200 --> 00:11:33.009
if I'm trying to lose weight, you know?

00:11:33.009 --> 00:11:34.010
So we figured out the chocolate

00:11:34.010 --> 00:11:35.690
chip cookies are not the problem.

00:11:35.690 --> 00:11:38.700
It's the guy eating the cookies.

00:11:38.700 --> 00:11:43.040
It's 80% behavior, it's
20% head knowledge.

00:11:43.040 --> 00:11:44.190
You know we really—

00:11:44.190 --> 00:11:47.960
you cannot work out enough to lose weight

00:11:47.960 --> 00:11:50.310
if you eat an elephant.

00:11:50.310 --> 00:11:52.020
I mean, you just can't do it.

00:11:52.020 --> 00:11:54.580
And the same thing is true
here with your money situation.

00:11:54.580 --> 00:11:57.280
You know, you cannot make enough money

00:11:57.280 --> 00:11:58.730
to outearn your stupidity.

00:11:58.730 --> 00:11:59.655
I tried it.

00:11:59.655 --> 00:12:01.470
I'm good at making money,

00:12:01.470 --> 00:12:05.160
but you have got to control
the person in your mirror.

00:12:05.160 --> 00:12:06.970
And once we understand that, then we go,

00:12:06.970 --> 00:12:08.520
well, if we're going to solve this—

00:12:08.520 --> 00:12:10.570
if it's a psychological behavior problem,

00:12:10.570 --> 00:12:12.010
then we're going to solve
it with a psychological

00:12:12.010 --> 00:12:14.480
behavior answer/solution.

00:12:14.480 --> 00:12:16.620
And so that's why the debt snowball works.

00:12:16.620 --> 00:12:17.710
And all these other theories,

00:12:17.710 --> 00:12:19.420
and all these people who
want to talk about this

00:12:19.420 --> 00:12:21.630
are just people that don't want to do it.

00:12:21.630 --> 00:12:22.940
They don't want to do the hard work

00:12:22.940 --> 00:12:24.960
