00:15:45.770 --> 00:15:47.040
or we're going to go on vacation.

00:15:47.040 --> 00:15:49.370
No, no, no, your operating expenses.

00:15:49.370 --> 00:15:52.130
Like, what is the amount
of money you need to have

00:15:52.130 --> 00:15:54.580
to keep the lights on, to
keep food on the table,

00:15:54.580 --> 00:15:57.990
to keep things operating
like they would be otherwise?

00:15:57.990 --> 00:16:00.360
That is what the emergency fund is for.

00:16:00.360 --> 00:16:02.730
It's there in case of a job loss,

00:16:02.730 --> 00:16:04.990
it's there in case of a medical emergency.

00:16:04.990 --> 00:16:08.930
Whatever comes up that is
unexpected and a big emergency—

00:16:08.930 --> 00:16:10.550
this fund is there to catch you.

00:16:10.550 --> 00:16:14.870
It's like your major safety
net between you and life.

00:16:14.870 --> 00:16:18.160
And you have to think
of this as insurance,

00:16:18.160 --> 00:16:20.380
not an investment.

00:16:20.380 --> 00:16:23.530
Say it with me through
your phone or computer:

00:16:23.530 --> 00:16:26.570
Insurance, not an investment.

00:16:26.570 --> 00:16:29.430
You're going to get a pile
of money saved in the bank

00:16:29.430 --> 00:16:31.470
and some of you out
there are going to be like,

00:16:31.470 --> 00:16:33.230
oh my gosh, we could invest this

00:16:33.230 --> 00:16:34.420
and make so much more money.

00:16:34.420 --> 00:16:36.660
It's just sitting there, making nothing.

00:16:36.660 --> 00:16:38.140
Listen, that is what it is for.

00:16:38.140 --> 00:16:40.040
You have to think of this as insurance.

00:16:40.040 --> 00:16:42.210
Because you want to be
able to keep it liquid—

00:16:42.210 --> 00:16:44.510
you wanna be able to get to it quickly.

00:16:44.510 --> 00:16:48.010
So, I would recommend having
this in a money market account,

00:16:48.010 --> 00:16:50.690
or even you could do a
traditional savings account.

00:16:50.690 --> 00:16:54.340
