403(b)s, IRAs, or Roth IRAs.

00:19:08.210 --> 00:19:09.470
It's very important to set

00:19:09.470 --> 00:19:11.530
that money aside each and every month.

00:19:11.530 --> 00:19:14.360
So, you want to sign up to
where it's done automatically—

00:19:14.360 --> 00:19:15.830
it's not anything you have to think of.

00:19:15.830 --> 00:19:17.790
You can do that in your HR department

00:19:17.790 --> 00:19:19.300
as you enroll in your 401(k).

00:19:19.300 --> 00:19:21.240
But listen, make sure you get with

00:19:21.240 --> 00:19:23.170
an investment professional to guide you.

00:19:23.170 --> 00:19:25.680
They're a lot of options of
things that you can invest in,

00:19:25.680 --> 00:19:27.960
but you want to make sure you're
picking the right things.

00:19:27.960 --> 00:19:31.260
But as you do this 15%
of household income,

00:19:31.260 --> 00:19:34.460
over time what'll happen is
you'll start to build wealth.

00:19:34.460 --> 00:19:36.790
This is not money for a
down payment on a home.

00:19:36.790 --> 00:19:38.340
This is not money for a wedding,

00:19:38.340 --> 00:19:40.420
and Rachel, it's not money for a vacation.

